<br>
<br>
         The tiger had worked its way from the forks in the road, around midnight to the gates of Scynthia. The creature never stopped, the pouch and letter it carried around its neck, was important and needed to get to the door of Wulf Heracles Darkshade-Loire.<br>
<br>
         The sun was now, just rising, as it was on Dawn's body, when the tiger stood before Wulf's door, pawing and scratching eagerly at the wood. <br>
<br>
         Once the door was opened the tiger pawed past the male amazon, and jumped atop the bed. Dropping the leather pouch, and the scroll from its neck. The leather pouch landed softly atop the bed, the half heart shaped locket rolled gently out of the pouch and onto the bed, landing atop the unrolled scroll.<br>
<br>
         The scroll was written in a familiar handwriting, and only ment more heartache.<br>
<br>
   Dear Wulf,<br>
<br>
I told you so many months ago, that I would be going. I never did, and I must have sounded like a fool, thinking I knew what I was talking about. But I am going, I am gone. You'll find me on the fork between the three villages you and I have lived in our entire lives. <br>
<br>
I have a secret for you son, that contains that heart shaped locket you have. When the time is right, reunite your locket with Hippolytes, then take a hammer to them, and smash them. I cannot tell you what will happen, but I can tell you I will return reincarnated. <br>
<br>
For now. . if I am buried with the ancients, you will always have me in spirit. I'll visit when they allow, I promise. <br>
<br>
This is never goodbye, my son. This is just a new beginning.. always remember that I love you.<br>
<br>
Dawnithinia Rivent Darkshade  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#993300>- </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite>Amazons Unite</a><font color=#993300> - </font><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6>Amazons of the Northern Lands</a> <font color=#993300> - </font><a href="http://www.amazonsunite.i-p.com">Home</a><font color=#993300> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.4 b8<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  